03/11/2004
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Opposition presidential candidate Traian Basescu met with the Foreign Investors Council in Bucharest on Tuesday (2 November) and vowed to strengthen the fight against corruption if he wins the 28 November election. 
The Bucharest mayor is running as the candidate of the National Liberal Party-Democratic Party opposition alliance. 
He describes corruption as the main enemy of national security. 
(Nine o'clock - 02/11/04)
